With this Git repository, the benchmark experiments and Figures 4,5, and 6 can be reproduced.  
Please note that the analyses in the paper were performed using a high-throughput batch system.  
The system used consists of 11 nodes with 96 GB to 768 GB memory and 12 to 64 CPUs.  

This repository implements the same calculations on a local system, which may result in long computation times.  

To run the benchmark experiments and generate the plots, please follow these steps:
1) Download all benchmark data sets you want to use from the UCI repository. Detailed information about the data sets are given in Table A.1 in the publication.
2) Store the downloaded data in the folder external_data. Please use one folder per data set (see functions/get_cv_data.R for details regarding naming the folders), 
e.g. store the wine data set like that "wineW/winequality-white.csv".
3) Open the R project "benchmark.Rproj".  
4) Run the script "01run_benchmark.R" to simulate the data. Details are provided in the script header.   
   You may choose a higher number of repetitions and simulated settings, but this will increase the runtime.  
5) Open the script "02figure4.R" and/or "02figure5.R" and/or "02figure6.R" to generate the plots based on the data from step 4.  

If you want to use the original data from the paper, please download the data from xxx and store it in the "data" folder.  
In the scripts ("02figure4.R", "02figure5.R", and "02figure6.R"), the corresponding lines for using this data are already included but commented out.  
Please uncomment these lines and comment out the lines that use the simulated data from the steps above.  

